cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with optimization of big data, which is a common topic in machine learning and data science. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are likely categories. The paper also proposes a novel parallel algorithm, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of random and deterministic procedures in the algorithm suggests that it may also fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
